<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="degree-n">degree <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /dɪ'ɡriː/    美 /dɪ'ɡriː/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 程度：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>first degree burns 
一度烧伤</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Reading a book requires a <strong>degree of</strong> active attention and devotion.
看书需要一定程度的专注和投入。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 度；度数：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>100 degrees Celsius 
摄氏100度</p></div>

<h4 id="3-c">3.★ <strong>[C] 学位：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>earn</strong> / <strong>get</strong> / <strong>receive</strong> / be awarded <strong>a degree in</strong> Economics
取得经济学学位</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In most countries, a university degree can give you a flying start in life.  
在大多数国家，大学学位能给你的人生一个展翅高飞的起点。</p><footer>2010 四川</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="to-a-certain-degree-to-some-degree">to a (certain) degree / to some degree</h3>
<p>1.<strong>在 (一 定) 程度上；相当：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To a certain degree, it’s a matter of logic. 
在一定程度上，这是个逻辑问题。</p><footer>2011 北京</footer></div></div>